definition.value: Any deviation from the normal number of eosinophils per volume in the blood circulation.
The presence of virus in the blood.
Persistent presence of Epstein-Barr virus in the blood.
Nuclear or cytoplasmic aggregates of substances in red blood cells.
An infection of a hair follicle that extends subcutaneously, forming an abscess.

An infection resulting from live attenuated vaccines (LAV), that is, a vaccine prepared from living viruses or bacteria that have been weakened under laboratory conditions. LAV vaccines will replicate in a vaccinated individual and produce an immune response but usually cause mild or no disease. are derived from disease-causing pathogens.
Infection with the rubella virus of the live-attenuated vaccine.
Repeated episodes of the formation of abscesses in organs. An abscess is a circumscribed area of pus or necrotic debris in the parenchyma or an organ.

label.value: Prolonged need of intravenous antibiotic therapy

definition.value: Clinical assessment of a requirement to treat with intravenous antibiotics over an unusually prolonged period of time.
Increased susceptibility to streptococcal infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of streptococcal infections.
An unusual fungal infection that is regarded as a sign of a pathological susceptibility to infection by a fungal agent.
An unusual protozoan infection that is regarded as a sign of a pathological susceptibility to infection by a protozoal agent.
A partial or complete breakage of the continuity of a bone.

label.value: Abnormal CD4+CD25+ regulatory T cell proportion
Increased proportion of CD4+CD25+ regulatory T cells

definition.value: An abnormally increased proportion of CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cells in circulation, relative to another population of cells.

label.value: Decreased proportion of CD4+CD25+ regulatory T cells

definition.value: An abnormally decreased proportion of CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cells in circulation, relative to another population of cells.

label.value: Abnormal retinal nerve fiber layer morphology

definition.value: A structural abnormality of the retinal nerve fiber layer
Swelling (edema) of the retinal nerve fibers.
A lump detected in the prostate. In this context, mass is a general term for a lump or growth that may be caused by the abnormal growth of cells, a cyst, hormonal changes, or an immune reaction.

A lump detected in the region that surrounds a joint. In this context, mass is a general term for a lump or growth that may be caused by the abnormal growth of cells, a cyst, hormonal changes, or an immune reaction.
